        <p>
            You might be wondering what the difference between <Code Content="YWxpZ24tanVzdGlmeQ=="></Code> and <Code Content="YWxpZ24tc3BhY2Vk"></Code>is.
            A justified grid (<Code Content="anVzdGlmeS1jb250ZW50OiBzcGFjZS1iZXR3ZWVu"></Code>) evenly distributes the space between each column.
            The first and last columns pin to the edge of the grid.
        </p>
        <p>
            A spaced grid (<Code Content="anVzdGlmeS1jb250ZW50OiBzcGFjZS1hcm91bmQ="></Code>) evenly distributes the space around each column.
            This means there will always be space to the left of the first column, and to the right of the last column.
        </p>
        <p>
            The horizontal alignment classes are shorthands for the <Code Content="anVzdGlmeS1jb250ZW50"></Code> CSS property.
        </p>
